  <abstract>Engraving of the Clarksville Female Academy showing several women walking on a path around the outside of the building.</abstract>
  <abstract>The Clarksville Female Academy was organized in 1846 as the first girls' school in the area. During the Civil War, it was used by the Federal troops as a hospital. The school re-opened in 1866 after the building was repaired. In 1882 the original building was replaced.</abstract>
